column2: create table Session( --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- --/H a row for each request sequence (page view or sql events within # minutes) from an IP    ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- --/T sessions tell is a lot about the context of a web request or sql request. --/T We ignore anything but pageviews and ignore VO-registry and BigBrother admin traffic --/T ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 		sessionID         int identity not null primary key , 		FirstEventID      int not null,    --/D first request in the session id /R SessionLog 		IpID              int not null,    --/D ipAddress of client id /R ipMap 		startTime         datetime not null,  --/D when session started    		limitTime         datetime not null,  --/D when session ended    		seconds           int not null,    --/D duration  		events            int not null,    --/D number of web or sql requests in session  		HTTP              int not null,    --/D number of web requests in session 		SQL               int not null,    --/D number of sql requests in session 		spiderCount       int not null  default(#), --/D Spider hits to session (google or robots.txt) 		progCount         int not null  default(#), --/D programs: java, python, perl,.. 		browserCount      int not null  default(#), --/D browser client. 		sqlStems          int default(#),  --/D distinct sql templates 		webStems          int default(#)   --/D distinct web urls  		) go
